Based on the search results and content, here's how to set up a custom color palette for mobile-first responsive design in Tailwind CSS:

## Setting Up Custom Color Palettes in Tailwind CSS

### For Tailwind v3 (Most Common in 2024)

**1. Basic Custom Color (Single Shade)**

Add custom colors to your `tailwind.config.js` file:

```javascript
/** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
export default {
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        'brand-primary': '#FF5A1F',
        'brand-secondary': '#32CD32',
      },
    },
  },
}
```

**2. Custom Color with Multiple Shades**

For a full color scale (50-950):

```javascript
export default {
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        'brand': {
          50: '#f0f9ff',
          100: '#e0f2fe',
          200: '#bae6fd',
          300: '#7dd3fc',
          400: '#38bdf8',
          500: '#0ea5e9',
          600: '#0284c7',
          700: '#0369a1',
          800: '#075985',
          900: '#0c4a6e',
          950: '#082f49',
        },
      },
    },
  },
}
```

**3. Replace Default Colors (Smaller Bundle)**

To only use your custom colors and remove all defaults:

```javascript
export default {
  theme: {
    colors: {
      'primary': {
        50: '#f0f9ff',
        500: '#0ea5e9',
        900: '#0c4a6e',
      },
      'secondary': '#32CD32',
    },
  },
}
```

### For Tailwind v4 (Latest)

**1. CSS-First Approach with `@theme`**

Create your colors in CSS using the new `@theme` directive:

```css
/* app.css */
@import "tailwindcss";

@theme {
  /* Brand colors */
  --color-primary-50: oklch(98.3% 0.02 250);
  --color-primary-100: oklch(95.1% 0.03 250);
  --color-primary-500: oklch(68% 0.1 250);
  --color-primary-900: oklch(30% 0.1 250);

  /* Single accent color */
  --color-accent: #FF5A1F;
}
```

**2. Disable Default Colors (v4)**

```css
@tailwind base;
@theme {
  --disable-default-colors: true;

  /* Your custom palette */
  --color-brand-50: #F5F5FA;
  --color-brand-500: #5B5BD6;
  --color-brand-900: #0D0D3B;
}
```

### Mobile-First Responsive Usage

Once configured, use your custom colors with Tailwind's mobile-first breakpoints:

```html
<!-- Mobile first: starts with mobile, then tablets, then desktop -->
<div class="bg-brand-500 md:bg-brand-600 lg:bg-brand-700">
  <h1 class="text-brand-50 md:text-brand-100">
    Responsive Heading
  </h1>
</div>

<!-- Responsive with custom colors -->
<button class="
  bg-primary-500 hover:bg-primary-600
  text-white
  px-4 py-2 
  md:px-6 md:py-3
  lg:px-8 lg:py-4
">
  Click Me
</button>
```

### Using Arbitrary Color Values

For one-off colors without configuration:

```html
<div class="bg-[#1e40af] text-[#f0f9ff]">
  Custom color without config
</div>
```

### Runtime Theme Switching (Dark Mode)

```css
@theme {
  --color-surface: #FFFFFF;
  --color-content: #111827;
}

html.dark @theme {
  --color-surface: #1F2937;
  --color-content: #F9FAFB;
}
```

```html
<html class="dark">
  <body class="bg-surface text-content">
    Content adapts to theme
  </body>
</html>
```

### Helpful Tools

- **Tailwind Color Palette Generator** (Elementor): Generate full color scales from a single color
- **Tailwind Eye Dropper**: Chrome extension to pick colors from websites and convert to Tailwind
- **Figma Tailwind Color Palettes**: Plugin to use Tailwind colors in Figma designs
- **oklch.com**: Convert hex colors to OKLCH format for Tailwind v4

## Sources:
- [The Ultimate Guide to Tailwind Colors and Personalizing Them - Blogs](https://blogs.purecode.ai/blogs/tailwind-colors)
- [Tailwind v4 Colors: Add & Customize Fast | Tailkits](https://tailkits.com/blog/tailwind-v4-custom-colors/)

